Years later, he's finally in a position to manipulate the current admin to his way of thinking.  Time Mag's article on how we got to war depicts Wolfowitz as a central figure in pushing that agenda.<br>
<br>
Anyway, at the website I listed, hit the link to their statement of principles.  Look at the date and look at the signatures.  Many people in power now were founders of PNAC (1997).  Click the other links on the middle east from their early writings and you'll see that they've been calling for Saddam's overthrow for a long time.  Has nothing to do with WMD's or anything like that.<br>
<br>
Although I'm not a conspiracy theorist or the like, I too believe that the motivation was actually protection of Israel.  Wolfowitz, Richard Perle and several others are Zionists.  They serve two masters.....their solemn duty to protect Israel (read Richard Perle's writings sometime and Wolfowitz') while serving in the US government.<br>
<br>
While I don't believe they'd compromise the US standing to carry out this mission, I do think they'd start a war not wholly in US interest to get it done.  Saddam wasn't funding al Qaeda, but he was funding occasionally anti Israeli activities through Hamas, etc.  Wolfowitz has been after him for years and years.  <br>
<br>
Here is their 1998 letter to Clinton, also on their own website, at the letters link.  While they continue to prattle on about the WMD, that's not really the reason.  Wolfowitz had been calling Saddam an imminent threat since the early '90's.  He was, but not to the US.  Please keep in mind that this is PNAC's own website;  not a website somebody else set up about them.  They're quite proud of themselves and feel they have nothing to hide.<br>
